        <title>Collaboration Tools</title>
        <contents>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are multiple ways to collaborate with our teammates or co-workers; you need to decide for yourselves what works best. Some of them will be tools that you already use, some will not. Some require registration but this list, as this is created, is not exhaustive, it is merely a compilation of tools that are the most common at this time and are free or have a limited free version. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;[VISUAL]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Here are just some of the ways that you can plan the different aspects of your collaboration:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tools for online collaboration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Miro&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mural&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Google products (Jamboard, Docs, Slides)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Padlet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ways to stay in touch (text or video) with teammates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Slack&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;WhatsApp&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Microsoft Teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Google Meet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Zoom&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ways to organise your teamâ€™s work&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Trello&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Asana&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Google Docs/Sheets&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tools for presentations for pitching&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Google Slides&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Canva&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;PowerPoint&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are so many digital ways to keep in touch and work together online that even if you are not in the same location, there should be a way to collaborate!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span&gt;After completing this Chapter, you should be able to:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Identify the elements of the entrepreneurial mindset and recognise that they are learnable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Explain the Service Design Process and the Design Sprint Process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Describe how service design can help in developing services in a knowable and repeatable manner&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Know what tools can be used for in-person and online collaboration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</contents>
